{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"[G3 child-coverage — container review of parent 1f19-adf2-ffb2-4b09 paired with THIS child (S6 1ba5: Docs — private-repo credentials, descriptive errors, ref/source semantics, HMAC trust model)]\n\nAudited this child's contribution to the parent's acceptance/success criteria; every absence cross-checked against the WHOLE sibling roster (S1 6d56, S2 70c7, S3 fa49, S4 30b3, S5 b7fa). This child is the DOCUMENTATION slice; the union of children covers every parent criterion. No uncovered parent criterion. Empty G3 findings list.\n\n4-bucket coverage map (parent AC -> covering child/children; this child's role called out):\n- Parent AC1 (no attested gate reads the working tree; all read a faithful snapshot at the pinned SHA) — FULLY covered by S1 (6d56 materialize core) + S3 (fa49 gate re-rooting). STRUCTURAL w.r.t. this child (its Scope: \"Out: code (S1-S5)\"); claims none. Not an absence.\n- Parent AC2 (signed verdict records verified_at_sha + reproducible over identical content) — FULLY covered by S4 (30b3 record+sign+in-toto) atop the immutable-SHA basis from S1. This child contributes the DOCS half: its AC3 (ref/source semantics, origin/main default, signs-vs-never-signs + verified_at_sha recording documented for CLI and MCP) + its AC4 (HMAC trust model + limits + in-toto Statement shape documented). STRUCTURAL w.r.t. the signing behavior (S4). Not an absence.\n- Parent AC3 (local mode reads in-place checkout AND cannot produce a signed verdict) — behavior covered by S3 (in-place read) + S4 (signing bar). This child DOCUMENTS the attested-signs vs local-never-signs semantics (its AC3) and the fail-closed (attested) vs local-still-runs behavior (its AC2). Docs co-role; no uncovered half. Not an absence.\n- Parent AC4 (concurrent gates, no git-lock contention / cross-op corruption; atomic population; delete-on-last-close) — FULLY covered by S1 (atomic population) + S2 (single-flight, delete-on-last-close). STRUCTURAL w.r.t. this child. Not an absence.\n- Parent AC5 (snapshot cache + janitor reclaim under pressure without disrupting in-flight reads) — behavior FULLY covered by S2. This child DOCUMENTS the disk-cap behavior (its AC5). STRUCTURAL w.r.t. the mechanism. Not an absence.\n- Parent AC6 (private-repo fetch failure surfaces a descriptive, actionable credential error) — FULLY covered, with THIS child as the DOCS PRIMARY OWNER: its AC1 (README MCP-setup section + docs/jira-sync-setup.md state the private-repo fetch-credential requirement and how to supply it, grep-able) + its AC2 (the descriptive missing-credential error message + remedy AND the fail-closed-attested/local-still-runs behavior documented in a named file). S1 (6d56 AC5) RAISES the actionable error; this child DOCUMENTS message+remedy. Implementation + named-doc-owner pairing is complete. Clean.\n- Parent AC7 (portable: no external tar; no hardcoded /tmp; flock+mkdir fallback) — implementation FULLY covered by S1 (6d56 AC4 + portability seam). This child DOCUMENTS REBAR_GATE_TMPDIR + the EFS/NFS flock caveat (its AC5, xref alto-fruit-punch). Implementation + docs split clean. Not an absence.\n- Parent AC8 (all six child stories closed; make lint + full test suite green) — STRUCTURAL/meta epic-completion criterion; covered by the existence of all six children (this child is story #6 of 6 in the roster) + each child's own green-bar obligation. Not an absence at this child.\n\nSuccess-criteria narrative (\"every code-reading gate verifies a client-specified, immutable, reproducible snapshot ... never the server's mutable checkout ...; signed verdicts reproducible and bound to verified_at_sha; unsigned local preserves verify-before-push\") decomposes onto AC1-AC3/AC6. This child carries the OPERATIONAL/TRUST-MODEL DOCUMENTATION surface that the snapshot model newly requires: the fetch-credential prerequisite (new vs the old read-the-checkout model), the descriptive failure behavior, the attested-signs/local-never-signs + origin/main + verified_at_sha semantics, the HMAC trust model + limits + in-toto Statement shape, and the new env/knob (REBAR_GATE_TMPDIR) + disk-cap + EFS/NFS flock caveat. No uncovered obligation is introduced by this child's existence.\n\nCross-referenced named-consumer hand-offs that land on THIS child (covered-by-named-consumer, not absences elsewhere):\n- S4 (30b3) defers its HMAC-trust-model docs explicitly to S6 (\"its limits ... are DOCUMENTED in S6\"; its AC5 hand-off) — claimed here by this child's AC4.\n- S1 (6d56) defers the descriptive credential MESSAGE detail to S6 (\"see S6\") — claimed here by this child's AC2.\n- S5 (b7fa) defers ref/source PROSE semantics to S6 — claimed here by this child's AC3 (schema-text vs prose split is clean; S5 surfaces inline schema text, S6 owns the human prose).\nEach cross-ref resolves to a concrete AC on this child; no docs obligation named by a sibling is left unclaimed.\n\nNote (scope, not a G3 finding): the standing G4 dependency-gap finding on sibling S4 (30b3) about routing the pinned-SHA snapshot handle into plan_review/attest.py's dependency_hashes()/_rehash()/claim-gate freshness re-check is a code seam between S3 and S4; it is a CONSISTENCY (G4) concern, unrelated to this docs child, and does not leave any parent criterion unclaimed (AC1/AC2/ref-coherence remain claimed by children). G3 union-coverage of the parent criteria is complete.\n\nConclusion: this child cleanly covers the documentation slice (private-repo fetch-credential requirement, descriptive credential-error + fail-closed-vs-local behavior, ref/source + signing/verified_at_sha semantics, HMAC trust model + limits + in-toto Statement shape, REBAR_GATE_TMPDIR/disk-cap/EFS-NFS-flock knobs) of the parent criteria — it is the docs primary owner of parent AC6 and the docs half of AC2/AC3/AC5/AC7; no parent acceptance/success criterion is left uncovered by the roster. No G3 finding for this pairing."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782526550503822001,"uuid":"3627ce2e-950d-42dc-aa09-f1987d519532"}